        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down.</placeName>
                    <date>Sept. 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I enclose a draft for <hi rend="superscript">£</hi>10<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> 100 due tomorrow (ie 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>) as I believe.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I return you my very sincere thanks for all your great kindness &amp; assistance to my Boys. I cannot say how I regret for our own sake your projected African Expedition. I yet hope it may be deferred, at least till the Spring.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>My dear Sir | Yours very sincerely | C. Darwin</p>
<p>P.S. | My servant will call after 12 oclock for the Arum plant for which I am much obliged.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">3.1 after] ‘a’ <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘one’</note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is given by an entry in CD’s Account book recording the payment mentioned in the letter (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">An entry dated 26 September 1859 in CD’s Account book (Down House MS) indicates that this sum was paid to Reed. Reed was tutoring <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1222.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Francis Darwin</ref>. He had formerly tutored <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1224.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">George Howard Darwin</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">It is not known whether Reed visited Africa. CD continued to pay him for tutorials in 1860.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2474.xml" resp="#automat">letter to G. V. Reed, 1 July [1859]</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
